g.text: Note1: do we make a single thread responsable for
extracting urls, hashing & checking and storing urls ?
or do we make each url responsable for this process itself
Note: This is an I/O op so it takes a lot of time,
writing to it one URL at a time is inefficient.
Maybe hash & check all URLs then write to file.
Note2: why do we need to use the whole content of the page to
hash and store the page ? can't we use the URL ?
Note: keep a counter to check for num
Also note that counter is shared between threads
1- We are performing a lot of I/O operations to store the state of visited pages.
2- We need to think of a way to handle priority. (Most likely we would use a single HPF queue)
